HB 39 Original 2026 Regular Session Firment
Abstract: Requires peace officers to be citizens of the United States.
Present law provides for qualifications, requirements, and training requirements for all peace
officers in La.
Present federal law defines "United States citizen" as any individual who is a citizen of the
United States by law, birth, or naturalization.
Proposed law requires all persons seeking to be a peace officer in La. to be a United States
citizen as defined in federal law.
(Adds R.S. 40:2402(5) and 2404.4)
